headlines.description: — LaMelo Ball and Miles Bridges each scored 23 points and the Charlotte Hornets held on to beat the Dallas Mavericks 110-105 on Monday to extend their winning streak to a season-high three games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ball, Bridges each score 23 to lead Hornets over Mavs 110-105 for 3rd straight win

headlines.description: — Cade Cunningham had 32 points, nine rebounds and seven assists to lead the Detroit Pistons to a 107-96 win over the Houston Rockets on Monday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cunningham scores 32 points to lead the Pistons over the Rockets 107-96

headlines.description: — Jaren Jackson Jr. had 24 points, including 15 in the fourth quarter, and Desmond Bane added 22 points as the Memphis Grizzlies used a late rally to beat the Minnesota Timberwolves 108-106 on Monday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jackson, Bane lead 4th-quarter rally as Grizzlies beat Timberwolves 108-106

events.name: Atlanta Hawks at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Jalen Brunson scored 34 points to lead the New York Knicks to a 119-110 win over the Atlanta Hawks on Monday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jalen Brunson scores 34 to lead Knicks over Hawks 119-110

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell scored 33 points — 23 in the second half — and Darius Garland added 16 as the Cleveland Cavaliers began the season's unofficial second half by dominating the Phoenix Suns 118-92 in a Martin Luther King Jr. Day matinee on Monday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Donovan Mitchell scores 33 points and propels NBA-leading Cavaliers to easy 118-92 win over Suns

events.name: Boston Celtics at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum scored 22 points, Kristaps Porzingis had 18 and the Boston Celtics handed the Golden State Warriors their most lopsided home loss in 40 years with a 125-85 victory on Monday.
headlines.shortLinkText: The Celtics hand the Warriors their most lopsided home loss in 40 years with a 125-85 win

events.name: Utah Jazz at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — CJ McCollum scored six of his 45 points in overtime and the New Orleans Pelicans orchestrated the largest comeback in franchise history, overcoming a 25-point deficit to beat Utah Jazz 123-119 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: McCollum leads Pelicans to franchise-best 25-point comeback in a 123-119 OT win over the Jazz

headlines.description: — Zach LaVine scored 35 points and the Chicago Bulls defeated the Los Angeles Clippers 112-99 on Monday night to snap a five-game skid.
headlines.shortLinkText: LaVine leads Bulls over Clippers 112-99 as Chicago snaps 5-game skid with rare win in back-to-back
